<span id="freeTextContainer7192666279897633544"><b>The Templar Legacy</b><br/>1 Star<br/><br/>This is my third attempt at reading this book and its time to call it quits. <br/><br/>The main character is interesting enough and the plot has potential, but it moves along at a snails pace with excessive descriptions of the scenery (villages, buildings, forests, gardens, etc.) and the innermost thoughts of each and every character most of whom I couldn&apos;t care less about. <br/><br/>Enough is enough!</span>
  <span id="freeText7192666279897633544" style="display:none"><b>The Templar Legacy</b><br />1 Star<br /><br />This is my third attempt at reading this book and its time to call it quits. <br /><br />The main character is interesting enough and the plot has potential, but it moves along at a snails pace with excessive descriptions of the scenery (villages, buildings, forests, gardens, etc.) and the innermost thoughts of each and every character most of whom I couldn't care less about. <br /><br />Enough is enough!</span>
